                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-164-victim1626 t18310217-164-viclabel987"></join>s, <placeName id="t18310217-164-crimeloc988">Size-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-164-crimeloc988" type="placeName" value="Size-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-164-crimeloc988" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-164-off985 t18310217-164-crimeloc988"></join>. There were two mats in their passage; one was chained to the door, and the other sewn to it. On Thursday last, about half-past five o'clock, I heard the chain make a noise, as if it was disturbed; I was in the kitchen; I ran up, and saw the<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183102170103"></xptr>prisoner with the mat in his hands, upright - I am certain he is the man; I said, "Oh! you thief," he dropped it, and walked away - he had separated it from the one which was chained - I went out after him, and I never lost sight of him; I laid hold of his coat; he broke from me, but was stopped by a gentleman - it was in the daytime.</p>
               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18310217-164-person1629">
                  CHARLES 
                  AUGUSTUS ROBERTS
               <interp inst="t18310217-164-person1629" type="surname" value="AUGUSTUS ROBERTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-164-person1629" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-164-person1629" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a merchant, and live in Bucklersbury - I saw the prisoner and witness disputing, and saw the prisoner break from her; she desired me to pursue, as he was a thief - he walked to the corner of Size-lane, then ran off; I followed, and stopped him - Fendick came up, and charged him with stealing the mat; he begged to be let go - I did not lose sight of him.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-164-person1630">
                  RICHARD 
                  GEORGE STATHAM
               <interp inst="t18310217-164-person1630" type="surname" value="GEORGE STATHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-164-person1630" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-164-person1630" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable - I received him in charge, and on his person found a screwdriver, a bag, a large knife, and two small screws - here is the mat; the string it is sewn with is cut.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. When the woman came out I was twenty yards from the door; she said, "You wretch, what have you been doing?" I said I had done no harm, and went round the corner; the gentleman laid hold of me - I have been out of employ a long time, and many days have not broken my fast for nine hours.</p>
